The transmissible spongiform encephalopathies (TSEs), or  prion  diseases, are neurodegenerative disorders which include Creutzfeldt to Jakob disease (CJD) and kuru in humans, bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE), transmissible mink encephalopathy, chronic wasting disease (CWD) in mule deer and elk, and scrapie in sheep and goats. Replication of the infectious TSE agent depends critically on the host prion protein (PrPc)
